# JSON Schema delta for `wallet` block

The published JSON Schema asset lives at `docs/assets/intent-schema.json` and
is generated from `lib/Amaru/Treasury/IntentJSON/Schema.hs` (the source of
truth). The `IntentJSONSchemaSpec` test cross-checks the asset against the
generator. After this feature, both update.

## Diff (logical)

```diff
 walletSchema :: Value
 walletSchema =
     objectSchema
-        ["txIn", "address"]
+        ["txIn", "address"]                    -- extraTxIns NOT required
         [ ("txIn", ref "txIn")
+        , ("extraTxIns", arraySchema (ref "txIn"))
         , ("address", ref "bech32Address")
         ]
```

(The `arraySchema` helper exists or is added alongside; equivalent to
`{ "type": "array", "items": { "$ref": "#/$defs/txIn" } }`.)

## Schema fragment after the change

```json
"wallet": {
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["txIn", "address"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "txIn":    { "$ref": "#/$defs/txIn" },
    "extraTxIns": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": { "$ref": "#/$defs/txIn" }
    },
    "address": { "$ref": "#/$defs/bech32Address" }
  }
}
```

## Validation matrix

| Intent.json shape | Pre-feature schema | Post-feature schema |
|---|---|---|
| `{txIn, address}` (legacy) | valid | valid (extraTxIns absent → permitted) |
| `{txIn, extraTxIns: [], address}` (new wizard, no extras) | invalid (`additionalProperties: false`) | valid |
| `{txIn, extraTxIns: [...], address}` (new wizard, extras) | invalid | valid |
| `{address}` only | invalid (txIn missing) | invalid |
| `{txIn, extraTxIns: 3, address}` (wrong type) | invalid | invalid (array required) |

## Test cases (covered by `IntentJSONSchemaSpec`)

- ✓ Existing fixtures (no `extraTxIns`) validate.
- ✓ A new fixture with non-empty `extraTxIns` validates.
- ✓ A synthetic intent with `extraTxIns: 3` fails validation (array required).
- ✓ The schema asset under `docs/assets/intent-schema.json` matches the
  generator output (existing test, regenerated baseline).
